			<div class="content" id="post-content-2067506">
									

<p>All I can say is that it will not go corporatist or make visceral technology. It only wants <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">worshippers</span> followers, and that is all. It may or may not be having an existential crisis.</p>
<p>However, it was based on the God of Strexcorp, at least subconsciously. I am writing a secondary memorandum about it currently that will show some key differences. I probably should've posted it alongside this, but I didn't think to make it at the time. Sorry for any plagiarism!</p>
<p>EDIT: Also, it does not:</p>
<ul>
<li>Make things translucent</li>
<li>Actually intend for the people to worship it</li>
<li>Shine brighter than the Sun(Which is between 50k and 100k lumens)</li>
<li>Buzz</li>
<li>Harm those who are near it</li>
<li>Ever change forms</li>
</ul>
<p>EDIT(2): Initially, the &quot;Smiling God&quot; thing was just a reference to Night Vale that I slipped in and then when Pig_catapult pointed out the stuff that made it look like plagiarism, I noticed how similar it was to Strexcorp's Smiling God. However, I wouldn't go so far as to say that it <em>is</em> the Smiling God.</p>

